      <item>
        <title>Student&#39;s t distribution</title>
        <description>&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;mean=\mu&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;variance=(\frac{c}{c-2})\sigma^2&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;parameter c is degrees of freedom. The variance approaches the one of the normal distribution for large c.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;t=\frac{\bar{X}-\mu}{S_X/\sqrt{n}}&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;{S_X}^2 = \frac{1}{n-1}\sum{(X_i-\bar{X})^2}&lt;/script&gt; is the standard deviation of the sample.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given some precalculated values from &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Student%27s_t-distribution&quot;&gt;Wikipedia&lt;/a&gt; statistics tables, we can find the associated probability.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
