        <category>statistics</category>
        
      </item>
    
      <item>
        <title>Generalized Extreme Value distribution (GEV)</title>
        <description>&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;gev(x) = exp(-(1+\frac{\xi(x-\mu)}{\sigma})^{\frac{-1}{\xi}})&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This distribution can be derived using the block maxima method: all observations x&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; are divided in equally spaced blocks. Then, we note the local maxima in each block. After normalization these maxima follow the GEV.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;\xi = 0&lt;/script&gt; : Gumbel distribution&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;% &lt;![CDATA[
\xi &lt; 0 %]]&gt;&lt;/script&gt; : Weibull distribution&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;\xi &gt; 0&lt;/script&gt; : Fréchet distribution&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Fréchet distribution shows significant &lt;strong&gt;fat tails&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
