      <item>
        <title>Durbin-Watson test</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Tests for first order &lt;code&gt;autocorrelation&lt;/code&gt;, i.e. between the value &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;u_t&lt;/script&gt; and the previous value &lt;script type=&quot;math/tex&quot;&gt;u_{t-1}&lt;/script&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;script type=&quot;math/tex; mode=display&quot;&gt;DW = \frac{ \Sigma_{t=2}^{T} (\hat{u}_t - \hat{u}_{t-1})^2} {\Sigma_{t=2}^{T} \hat{u}_t^2}&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The DW test can take values between 0 and 4.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;0&lt;/strong&gt;: positive autocorrelation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2&lt;/strong&gt;: no autocorrelation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4&lt;/strong&gt;: negative autocorrelation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So values near 2 indicate that the series does not exhibit autocorrelation.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
        <pubDate>Tue, 29 Mar 2016 00:44:01 +0200</pubDate>
        <link>http://codiepp.github.io/Hedge-o-Mat/Hedge-o-Mat/statistics/durbin-watson-test.html</link>
        <guid isPermaLink="true">http://codiepp.github.io/Hedge-o-Mat/Hedge-o-Mat/statistics/durbin-watson-test.html</guid>
        
        
        <category>statistics</category>
        
      </item>
    
      <item>
        <title>Coherent risk measure</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;A coherent risk measure satifies the following features:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;sub-additivity: ρ(R&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; + R&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;) ≤ ρ(R&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;) + ρ(R&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;monotonicity: ρ(R&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;) ≥ ρ(R&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;) if R&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; ≥ R&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;positive homogeneity: βρ(R) = ρ(βR), for all β&amp;gt;0.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;translation invariant: ρ(R) + c = ρ(c + R) for all constants c.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Beware! the &lt;a href=&quot;../methods/VAR&quot;&gt;VAR&lt;/a&gt; measure violates the first feature (sub-additivity).&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        <pubDate>Tue, 29 Mar 2016 00:44:01 +0200</pubDate>
